      "tagline": "Shoulders, Glutes & Posture",
      "weeks": "Weeks 1–5",
      "startDate": "2026-06-06",
      "endDate": "2026-07-10",
      "focuses": [
        "Groove the hip-dominant glute and posterior-shoulder patterns and build a posture base.",
        "Establish a recovery rhythm and a strong mind-muscle connection in the delts and glutes."
      ],
      "message": {
        "paragraphs": [
          "This first block isn't about chasing big numbers — it's about building the platform everything else stands on. Your job right now is to own the hip-hinge and shoulder patterns, wake up the glutes and rear delts that drive both your shape and your posture, and get your recovery working for you.",
          "Mentally, chase the feeling, not the load: every rep at the prescribed tempo, every squeeze felt exactly where it should be. By the end of five weeks you'll move cleaner, stand taller, feel your delts and glutes switch on the way they should — and you'll have laid the foundation for the visible change that starts in Cycle 2."
        ],
        "outcomes": [
          "Cleaner, more controlled hip-hinge and pressing patterns",
          "Glutes and rear delts that switch on when they should — real mind-muscle connection",
          "Better posture — shoulders sitting back, ribs and pelvis stacked",
          "A recovery rhythm that works for you: steadier sleep quality and protected rest days",
          "Confident tempo and RPE control on every main lift",
          "A foundation set for the visible change that starts in Cycle 2"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "num": 2,
      "name": "Growth Engine",
      "weeks": "Weeks 6–11",
      "focuses": [
        "Drive shoulder and glute hypertrophy with added volume and reps taken closer to failure.",
        "Progressively load the supported primaries — press, hip thrust, hack squat."
      ],
      "teaser": {
        "paragraphs": [
          "Cycle 2 is where the effort starts to show in the mirror. Once the foundation is set, we turn up the volume and let your shoulders and glutes genuinely begin to change shape. This is the block that rewards everything you bank now — but it only opens once you've earned it here.",
          "Build the base. Then we load it."
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "num": 3,
      "name": "Metabolic Shift",
      "weeks": "Weeks 12–16",
      "focuses": [
        "Strip body fat while preserving the muscle already built to sharpen overall shape.",
        "Hold training intensity in a deficit with strategic low-impact conditioning and steps."
      ]
    },
    {
      "num": 4,
      "name": "Strength Engine",
      "weeks": "Weeks 17–21",
      "focuses": [
        "Intensify load on the primary lifts to raise the strength ceiling that future growth sits on.",
